<h3 class="subsection"> 5.7.2 <code>lighter2</code> Developer's Manual </h3>

<a name="1"></a>
<h2 class="heading"> Introduction </h2>

<p>This section describes how <code>lighter2</code> options can be set from inside a
Crystal Space <tt>&lsquo;world&rsquo;</tt> file or library.  The effect of options will not 
be described in detail; refer to the &ldquo;User's Manual&rdquo; for a that.
</p>
<a name="2"></a>
<h2 class="heading"> General Syntax </h2>

<p><code>lighter2</code> options are set with the help of key-value-pairs:
</p>
<table><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><pre class="example">    ...
    &lt;key name=&quot;lighter2&quot; editoronly=&quot;yes&quot; <em>option</em>=<em>value</em> ... /&gt;
    ...
</pre></td></tr></table>
<p>Such a <samp>&lsquo;key&rsquo;</samp> node must be placed inside a <samp>&lsquo;meshobj&rsquo;</samp> node for mesh
object options respectively a <samp>&lsquo;meshfact&rsquo;</samp> node for mesh factory options.
</p>
<p>Here, <samp>&lsquo;name=&quot;lighter2&quot;&rsquo;</samp> is used by <code>lighter2</code> to identify keys 
containing options.  <samp>&lsquo;editoronly=&quot;yes&quot;&rsquo;</samp> instructs the engine to discard
the key-value-pair during normal execution in order to conserve memory (since
the <code>lighter2</code>-specific settings are simply not needed).  The actual
options are specified by a number of <samp>&lsquo;<em>option</em>=<em>value</em>&rsquo;</samp> pairs.
</p>
<a name="3"></a>
<h2 class="heading"> Available options </h2>

<dl compact="compact">
<dt> <code>vertexlight</code></dt>
<dd><p>Values: <samp>&lsquo;yes&rsquo;</samp>, <samp>&lsquo;no&rsquo;</samp>
</p>
<p>Enable per-vertex lighting.
</p>
</dd>
<dt> <code>lmscale</code></dt>
<dd><p>Values: floating point values
</p>
<p>Control lightmap density.
</p>
</dd>
<dt> <code>noselfshadow</code></dt>
<dd><p>Values: <samp>&lsquo;yes&rsquo;</samp>, <samp>&lsquo;no&rsquo;</samp>
</p>
<p>Disables casting of shadows from an object onto itself.
</p>
</dd>
</dl>


